    <!-- SERVICES -->
    <section class="services" id="services">
        <div class="section-label">What I do</div>
        <h2 class="section-heading" data-split>What I build for clients.</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Three ways I ship real systems — not dashboards, not demos.</p>
        <div class="services-stack">
            <div class="service-card">
                <div class="service-head">
                    <h3 class="service-title">Custom agent builds</h3>
                    <div class="service-tags">
                        <span class="service-tag">Architecture</span>
                        <span class="service-tag">Full-Stack</span>
                        <span class="service-tag">Multi-Agent</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="service-desc">Production agent systems designed and shipped solo. <strong>Onchain trade execution</strong> — a Rust/Go order-flow pipeline with real market feeds and MEV protection. <strong>Multi-agent coordination</strong> — persistent swarms with shared reasoning state across MCP servers. Architecture through deployment, in whatever stack the job needs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-card">
                <div class="service-head">
                    <h3 class="service-title">Automation infrastructure</h3>
                    <div class="service-tags">
                        <span class="service-tag">Workflows</span>
                        <span class="service-tag">Backends</span>
                        <span class="service-tag">Edge</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="service-desc">Real systems that remove manual work. <strong>Go monolith on Postgres + AWS</strong> — integrated event pipeline handling ingestion, enrichment, and delivery at scale. <strong>Edge products on Cloudflare Workers</strong> — serverless automation with D1, Queues, and R2. No dashboards, no demos — live production deployments.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service-card">
                <div class="service-head">
                    <h3 class="service-title">Developer tooling</h3>
                    <div class="service-tags">
                        <span class="service-tag">MCP</span>
                        <span class="service-tag">CLIs</span>
                        <span class="service-tag">Agents</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="service-desc">Tools that make agents and engineers more capable. <strong>Custom MCP servers</strong> — connecting LLMs to production APIs, databases, and file systems. <strong>Claude Code ecosystem</strong> — early ecosystem operator shaping how agents interact with code. CLI tooling, agent infrastructure, and the coordination layer for persistent intelligence.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

